="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-337_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">This is not just a day of reflection—it is a call to unite and act against the epidemic of violence, ensuring a safer and more just world for all women and girls.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-362_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iapVNj iUcVvL pf-357_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-341_">Organisations leading the fight to end femicide</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/multi-ethnic-group-of-happy-mature-women-holding-h-2023-11-27-04-54-25-utc.jpg?v=1709805280" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/multi-ethnic-group-of-happy-mature-women-holding-h-2023-11-27-04-54-25-utc.jpg?v=1709805280 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/multi-ethnic-group-of-happy-mature-women-holding-h-2023-11-27-04-54-25-utc_1000x.jpg?v=1709805280 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/multi-ethnic-group-of-happy-mature-women-holding-h-2023-11-27-04-54-25-utc_500x.jpg?v=1709805280 320w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Advocating for Women's Rights: International Day for the Elimination of Violence Against Women - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Advocating for Women's Rights: International Day for the Elimination of Violence Against Women - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bVHBsO cFdcpI pf-358_"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-360_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by gstockstudio via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-343_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">These organisations are leading the fight to end violence against women and support survivors:</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kMriOJ brNffh pf-354_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-345_"><b>UN Women</b> - Leading international initiatives to combat violence against women, UN Women drives policy changes, awareness campaigns, and global partnerships to promote gender equality and end femicide.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-347_"><b>Amnesty International</b> - Advocating for human rights, Amnesty campaigns against gender-based violence and discrimination, demanding justice and accountability for victims of femicide and other abuses.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-349_"><b>Women's Aid</b> - Providing life-saving support and refuge for survivors of domestic violence in the UK, Women’s Aid also works to prevent violence and empower women to rebuild their lives.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-351_"><b>Refuge</b> - Offering safe shelter, advocacy, and support services for women and children facing abuse, Refuge plays a vital role in protecting survivors and raising awareness about femicide.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-353_"><b>White Ribbon UK</b> - Engaging men and boys in the fight against violence, White Ribbon UK uses education and campaigns to challenge harmful attitudes and behaviours that perpetuate femicide and gender-based violence.</li></ul><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-356_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">These organisations are vital in the global movement to challenge injustice, support survivors, and create a safer world for women and girls. Together, their efforts reflect the power of collective action in addressing this urgent crisis.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-377_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iapVNj iUcVvL pf-376_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-368_">Key facts and statistics</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mohdizzuanbinroslan_340f74de-06dd-4abc-b801-6fd3eac90667.jpg?v=1709805351" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mohdizzuanbinroslan_340f74de-06dd-4abc-b801-6fd3eac90667.jpg?v=1709805351 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mohdizzuanbinroslan_340f74de-06dd-4abc-b801-6fd3eac90667_1000x.jpg?v=1709805351 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mohdizzuanbinroslan_340f74de-06dd-4abc-b801-6fd3eac90667_500x.jpg?v=1709805351 320w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Supporting Survivors: International Day 2024 Resources - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Supporting Survivors: International Day 2024 Resources - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bVHBsO cFdcpI pf-363_"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-365_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by mohdizzuanbinroslan via Envato Elements</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kMriOJ brNffh pf-375_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-370_">In 2024, the <strong>World Health Organisation</strong> reported that <strong>1 in 3 women globally</strong> have experienced physical or sexual violence at some point in their lives.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-372_">According to global data in 2024, a woman is killed <strong>every 10 minutes</strong> as a result of gender-based violence, emphasising the crisis of femicide.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-374_">In 2024, gender-based violence remains a broad issue, including not just physical abuse but also emotional, sexual, and financial coercion, alongside harmful practices such as <strong>forced marriage</strong> and <strong>female genital mutilation (FGM)</strong>.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-387_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iapVNj iUcVvL pf-382_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-379_">Conclusion </h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/woman-abuse-young-woman-scared-male-clenched-fis-2023-11-27-05-31-29-utc.jpg?v=1709805476" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/woman-abuse-young-woman-scared-male-clenched-fis-2023-11-27-05-31-29-utc.jpg?v=1709805476 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/woman-abuse-young-woman-scared-male-clenched-fis-2023-11-27-05-31-29-utc_1000x.jpg?v=1709805476 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/woman-abuse-young-woman-scared-male-clenched-fis-2023-11-27-05-31-29-utc_500x.jpg?v=1709805476 320w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Gender Equality Advocacy: International Day 2024 Campaigns - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Gender Equality Advocacy: International Day 2024 Campaigns - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bVHBsO cFdcpI pf-383_"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-385_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by rawf8 via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-381_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The <strong>International Day for the Elimination of Violence Against Women 2024</strong> is more than a day of recognition; it is a powerful call to action to address the stark reality that violence against women continues to devastate lives worldwide. With a woman killed every 10 minutes due to gender-based violence, this year's focus on femicide highlights the critical need for awareness, advocacy, and support for survivors.<br><br>As we stand at this pivotal moment, it is our collective responsibility to break the silence, challenge harmful norms, and demand systemic change. By raising awareness, supporting survivors, and holding perpetrators accountable, we can dismantle the structures that perpetuate this violence.<br><br>The fight to end violence against women is not just about addressing the present but securing a safer, more equitable future for all women and girls. Together, we can create a world where every woman lives with dignity, safety, and equality. Let us act now—because there are no excuses.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-9649" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-knuQPt cVHHwo pf-197_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-kRRxPL eBhmAi"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-198_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iapVNj iUcVvL pf-199_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-200_">Related blog articles</h3><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/blogs" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button2" class="sc-bBeLha dmngPZ pf-202_">View all</a></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-204_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:4;--c-md:4;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iapVNj iUcVvL pf-205_"><img alt="{{ article_560884514885.image.alt }}" loading="eager" width="{{ article_560884514885.image.width }}" height="{{ article_560884514885.image.height }}" src="{%- if article_560884514885.image -%}
